about.description: puremagic is a pure python module that will identify a file based off it's magic numbers.
about.summary: Pure python implementation of magic file detection

name: puremagic
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "puremagic" %}
{% set version = "1.4" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/cdgriffith/{{ name }}/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 10c5945014c34cf58155b4ec876abba3697d43a69f29db6fa4501298cbb7e6db

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - puremagic

about:
  home: https://github.com/cdgriffith/puremagic
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENCE
  summary: Pure python implementation of magic file detection

  description: |
    puremagic is a pure python module that will identify a file based off it's magic numbers.
  doc_url: https://github.com/cdgriffith/puremagic
  dev_url: https://github.com/cdgriffith/puremagic

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - andreyz4k
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.15
